    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**7 files** will be touched across 4 crates:\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` + new `StatsArgs` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs`)\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — **New file**: iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, computes per-bucket `DiskUsage`, prints `\"{bucket}: {size}\"` lines + `\"total: {total}\"`, supports `--human` flag\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` + re-export\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats`\n5. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` test helper + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter\n6. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;`\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — **New file**: 3 integration tests (empty raw, with packages raw, with packages human)\n\nKey design decisions:\n- **No preview feature gate** — unlike `cache_size` which is behind `PreviewFeature::CacheSize`, the requirements don't mention one, keeping the command immediately usable\n- **Reuses existing infrastructure** — `DiskUsage`, `human_readable_bytes`, `CacheBucket::iter()`, `CacheBucket::Display`, `Cache::bucket()`",
